title: Printer's Sample Book, 1877–78
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printed textiles. Contains 253 samples in a variety of designs.

tombstone.epitaph:
Printer's Sample Book, 1877–78.
1877–78. Medium: leather, paper, cotton. Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts. 1945-55-38.
